# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Rust / Cargo
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.orig
# The workspace Cargo.lock IS committed (a framework with binaries + reproducible
# CI), so it is intentionally NOT ignored.

# Coverage / profiling artifacts
*.profraw
*.profdata
/coverage
/lcov.info

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Book
#   - docs/book/book   : mdBook HTML output (regenerated by `make book`)
#   - docs/book/.venv  : local WeasyPrint toolchain (never commit a venv)
#   - docs/book/dist/  : the designed PDF + EPUB are committed release
#                        artifacts and are intentionally NOT ignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/docs/book/book
docs/book/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editors / IDEs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.idea/
/.vscode/
*.iml
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS noise
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local environment / secrets — never commit real credentials
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Internal tooling / planning artifacts — NOT part of the published framework.
# Agent/assistant project state, brainstorming specs, and the internal
# parity-analysis briefs stay local; they must never reach the public repo.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/
/docs/superpowers/
/docs/parity-briefs/
